<subSubSection id="1DDD31F6FF953532D0C0F9B2C66AF8D9" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5578627DFF953532D0C0F9B2C66AF8D9" blockId="15.[151,1436,1484,1832]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="67B3BE6FFF953532D0C0F9B2C46DF969" bold="true" box="[199,315,1663,1688]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was recently recorded for 
<collectingCountry id="2DD022EDFF953532D305F9B2C610F969" box="[770,838,1663,1688]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Brazil</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="31561F8CFF953532D373F9B2C198F969" box="[884,1230,1663,1688]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref18596" refString="Oliveira-da-Silva, A., Ale-da-Rocha, R. &amp; Rafael, J. A. (2006) Bionomia dos estagios imaturos de duas especies de Peckia (Diptera, Sarcophagidae) em suino em decomposicao em area de floresta no norte do Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 50, 524 - 527. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0085 - 56262006000400013" type="journal article">
Oliveira-da-Silva 
<emphasis id="67B3BE6FFF953532D439F94CC127F969" box="[1086,1137,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
, who reared more than 
<specimenCount id="43C1A9F4FF953532D0C9F969C423F94C" box="[206,373,1700,1725]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="generic">100 specimens</specimenCount>
from pig carcasses in Manaus (
<collectingRegion id="9703AC9FFF953532D2DCF969C60EF94D" box="[731,856,1700,1724]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
). These authors also reported some females, but we were not able to locate these specimens. Thus, the female remains undescribed. Like 
